---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Query Planner: How PostgreSQL Decides"
  description="Interactive visualization of PostgreSQL query planning — scan types, join strategies, EXPLAIN trees, cost model, and pg_stats"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "PostgreSQL", href: "/postgresql/" },
    { label: "Query Planner", href: "/postgresql/query-planner/" }
  ]}
>
<div class="viz-container">
  <header class="viz-header">
    <h1>🧠 Query Planner</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">How PostgreSQL Decides to Scan, Join, and Sort</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="overview-section">
    <div class="overview-card">
      <p>
        Every SQL query goes through the <strong>planner/optimizer</strong> before execution. PostgreSQL
        evaluates many possible plans — different scan methods, join orders, join algorithms — and picks
        the one with the <em>lowest estimated cost</em>. The cost model uses <strong>table statistics</strong>
        (row counts, value distributions, correlation) combined with configurable cost parameters to
        estimate I/O and CPU work. Understanding the planner means understanding <em>why</em> your
        query is slow — and how to fix it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Scan Types -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>🔍 Scan Types: How Rows Are Found</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">The planner chooses a scan method based on selectivity, table size, and index availability.</p>

    <div class="scan-controls">
      <div class="scan-slider">
        <label>Table rows: <strong id="scanRowsValue">100,000</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="scanRowsSlider" min="100" max="10000000" value="100000" step="100">
      </div>
      <div class="scan-slider">
        <label>Selectivity (% of rows matched): <strong id="scanSelectValue">5%</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="scanSelectSlider" min="0" max="100" value="5" step="1">
      </div>
      <div class="scan-check">
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="scanIndexExists" checked> B-tree index exists on filter column</label>
      </div>
      <div class="scan-check">
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="scanCovering"> Index covers all selected columns (index-only possible)</label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scan-result" id="scanResult">
      <div class="scan-chosen">
        <div class="scan-chosen-label">Planner chooses:</div>
        <div class="scan-chosen-name" id="scanChosenName">Index Scan</div>
        <div class="scan-chosen-reason" id="scanChosenReason">Low selectivity + index available</div>
      </div>
      <div class="scan-comparison" id="scanComparison">
        <!-- filled by JS -->
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="scan-cards">
      <div class="scan-card" id="scanCardSeq">
        <div class="scan-card-icon">📄</div>
        <h3>Sequential Scan</h3>
        <p>Reads every page in order. Cheapest for large result sets or small tables. Uses <code>seq_page_cost</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scan-card" id="scanCardIndex">
        <div class="scan-card-icon">🌳</div>
        <h3>Index Scan</h3>
        <p>Traverses B-tree, then fetches heap tuples. Best for very selective queries. Random I/O per row.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scan-card" id="scanCardIndexOnly">
        <div class="scan-card-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>Index-Only Scan</h3>
        <p>All columns in the index — no heap fetch needed (if visibility map says page is all-visible).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scan-card" id="scanCardBitmap">
        <div class="scan-card-icon">🗺️</div>
        <h3>Bitmap Scan</h3>
        <p>Builds a bitmap of matching pages, then fetches them in order. Best for medium selectivity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Join Strategies -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>🔗 Join Strategies</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Three join algorithms, each optimal for different data sizes. Drag the sliders to see the planner switch.</p>

    <div class="join-controls">
      <div class="join-slider">
        <label>Left table rows: <strong id="joinLeftValue">10,000</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="joinLeftSlider" min="10" max="10000000" value="10000" step="10">
      </div>
      <div class="join-slider">
        <label>Right table rows: <strong id="joinRightValue">1,000</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="joinRightSlider" min="10" max="10000000" value="1000" step="10">
      </div>
      <div class="join-check">
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="joinIndexExists"> Index on join column (right table)</label>
      </div>
      <div class="join-check">
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="joinPreSorted"> Both inputs pre-sorted</label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="join-result">
      <div class="join-chosen">
        <div class="join-chosen-label">Planner chooses:</div>
        <div class="join-chosen-name" id="joinChosenName">Hash Join</div>
        <div class="join-chosen-reason" id="joinChosenReason">Best for medium-large unsorted inputs</div>
      </div>
      <div class="join-costs" id="joinCosts">
        <!-- filled by JS -->
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="join-cards">
      <div class="join-card" id="joinCardNested">
        <div class="join-card-header nested">Nested Loop</div>
        <div class="join-card-body">
          <p>For each outer row, scan inner table. O(N×M) without index, O(N×log M) with. Best when one side is tiny.</p>
          <div class="join-card-cost" id="nestedCost">—</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="join-card" id="joinCardHash">
        <div class="join-card-header hash">Hash Join</div>
        <div class="join-card-body">
          <p>Build hash table on smaller input, probe with larger. O(N+M). Needs memory for hash table (work_mem).</p>
          <div class="join-card-cost" id="hashCost">—</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="join-card" id="joinCardMerge">
        <div class="join-card-header merge">Merge Join</div>
        <div class="join-card-body">
          <p>Walk both sorted inputs in lockstep. O(N+M) if pre-sorted; add O(N log N + M log M) for sorting.</p>
          <div class="join-card-cost" id="mergeCost">—</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: EXPLAIN Visualizer -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>📊 EXPLAIN Visualizer</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">Paste an EXPLAIN (or EXPLAIN ANALYZE) output to see it as an interactive tree.</p>

    <div class="explain-input-area">
      <textarea id="explainInput" placeholder="Paste EXPLAIN output here, e.g.:
Nested Loop  (cost=0.29..8.53 rows=1 width=16)
  ->  Index Scan using users_pkey on users  (cost=0.29..8.31 rows=1 width=8)
        Index Cond: (id = 42)
  ->  Seq Scan on orders  (cost=0.00..20.12 rows=3 width=8)
        Filter: (user_id = 42)" rows="8"></textarea>
      <div class="explain-actions">
        <button id="parseExplainBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">🌳 Parse Plan</button>
        <button id="loadSampleBtn" class="action-btn step-btn">📝 Load Sample</button>
        <button id="clearExplainBtn" class="action-btn reset-btn">🔄 Clear</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explain-tree-container" id="explainTreeContainer" style="display: none;">
      <div class="explain-tree" id="explainTree"></div>
      <div class="explain-tree-legend">
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot scan-dot"></span> Scan</span>
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot join-dot"></span> Join</span>
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot sort-dot"></span> Sort/Aggregate</span>
        <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-dot other-dot"></span> Other</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: pg_stats -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>📈 Statistics: What the Planner Knows</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">The planner relies on pg_stats — collected by ANALYZE — to estimate row counts and plan costs.</p>

    <div class="stats-demo">
      <div class="stats-table">
        <div class="stats-header">
          <span>Column: users.country</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stats-rows">
          <div class="stats-row">
            <span class="stats-key">n_distinct</span>
            <span class="stats-val" id="statsDistinct">42</span>
            <span class="stats-desc">Estimated distinct values</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-row">
            <span class="stats-key">null_frac</span>
            <span class="stats-val" id="statsNull">0.02</span>
            <span class="stats-desc">Fraction of NULL values</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-row">
            <span class="stats-key">most_common_vals</span>
            <span class="stats-val mcv" id="statsMCV">US, DE, GB, FR, JP</span>
            <span class="stats-desc">Most frequent values</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stats-row">
            <span class="stats-key">most_common_freqs</span>
            <span class="stats-val mcv" id="statsMCF">0.30, 0.15, 0.12, 0.08, 0.06</span>
            <span class="stats-desc">Their frequencies</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats-histogram">
        <div class="stats-histogram-title">Frequency Distribution (most_common_vals)</div>
        <div class="stats-bars" id="statsBars">
          <!-- filled by JS -->
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats-estimator">
        <label>WHERE country = <select id="statsCountrySelect">
          <option value="US">US (30%)</option>
          <option value="DE">DE (15%)</option>
          <option value="GB">GB (12%)</option>
          <option value="FR">FR (8%)</option>
          <option value="JP">JP (6%)</option>
          <option value="OTHER">Other (29%)</option>
        </select></label>
        <div class="stats-estimate" id="statsEstimate">
          <span class="stats-est-label">Estimated rows:</span>
          <span class="stats-est-value" id="statsEstRows">30,000</span>
          <span class="stats-est-detail" id="statsEstDetail">= 100,000 rows x 0.30 frequency</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Explanation: Why statistics matter -->
  <section class="explain-section">
    <div class="explain-card highlight-card">
      <h3>💡 Why Stale Statistics Cause Bad Plans</h3>
      <p>
        If you load 10 million rows but never run <code>ANALYZE</code>, the planner still thinks the table
        has its old row count. It might choose a sequential scan for a query that should use an index, or
        a nested loop join when a hash join would be 1000x faster. <strong>Autovacuum runs ANALYZE
        automatically</strong>, but after bulk loads you should run it manually:
        <code>ANALYZE tablename;</code>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Cost Model -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>⚙️ Cost Model Parameters</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">The planner's cost estimates depend on these GUC parameters. Adjust them to see how plans change.</p>

    <div class="cost-controls">
      <div class="cost-slider">
        <label>seq_page_cost: <strong id="seqPageCostValue">1.0</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="seqPageCostSlider" min="0" max="40" value="10" step="1">
        <span class="cost-hint">Cost of a sequential disk page fetch</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-slider">
        <label>random_page_cost: <strong id="randomPageCostValue">4.0</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="randomPageCostSlider" min="0" max="100" value="40" step="1">
        <span class="cost-hint">Cost of a random disk page fetch (SSD ≈ 1.1, HDD ≈ 4.0)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-slider">
        <label>cpu_tuple_cost: <strong id="cpuTupleCostValue">0.01</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="cpuTupleCostSlider" min="1" max="100" value="10" step="1">
        <span class="cost-hint">CPU cost per row processed</span>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-slider">
        <label>effective_cache_size: <strong id="cacheSizeValue">4 GB</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="cacheSizeSlider" min="1" max="128" value="4" step="1">
        <span class="cost-hint">Planner's estimate of available cache (OS + shared_buffers)</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cost-scenario">
      <div class="cost-scenario-title">Scenario: SELECT * FROM orders WHERE customer_id = 42</div>
      <div class="cost-scenario-info">Table: 1M rows, 8 KB pages, ~125,000 pages. Index on customer_id. Query matches ~100 rows.</div>
      <div class="cost-comparison" id="costComparison">
        <!-- filled by JS -->
      </div>
      <div class="cost-verdict" id="costVerdict">
        <!-- filled by JS -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 6: Interactive Strategy Switcher -->
  <section class="flow-section">
    <h2>🎯 Strategy Switcher: Watch the Planner Think</h2>
    <p class="section-desc">A realistic query scenario. Adjust parameters and watch the planner switch between strategies in real time.</p>

    <div class="strategy-controls">
      <div class="strategy-slider">
        <label>orders table rows: <strong id="stratOrdersValue">1,000,000</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="stratOrdersSlider" min="1000" max="50000000" value="1000000" step="1000">
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-slider">
        <label>customers table rows: <strong id="stratCustomersValue">50,000</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="stratCustomersSlider" min="100" max="5000000" value="50000" step="100">
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-slider">
        <label>WHERE selectivity: <strong id="stratSelectValue">1%</strong></label>
        <input type="range" id="stratSelectSlider" min="0" max="100" value="1" step="1">
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-check">
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="stratIndex" checked> Index on orders.customer_id</label>
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-check">
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="stratSSD" checked> SSD storage (low random_page_cost)</label>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="strategy-plan" id="strategyPlan">
      <!-- filled by JS -->
    </div>

    <div class="strategy-explain" id="strategyExplain">
      <p>Adjust the sliders above to see how the planner builds different execution plans.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="viz-footer">
    <p>Based on <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/planner-optimizer.html" target="_blank">PostgreSQL Planner Documentation</a> and <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/using-explain.html" target="_blank">Using EXPLAIN Guide</a></p>
  </footer>

  <div class="share-buttons">
    <span>Share this visualization:</span>
    <a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Interactive%20visualization%20of%20PostgreSQL%20Query%20Planner&url=https://systeminternals.dev/postgresql/query-planner/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">𝕏 Twitter</a>
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url=https://systeminternals.dev/postgresql/query-planner/" target="_blank" class="share-btn">in LinkedIn</a>
    <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/submitlink?u=https://systeminternals.dev/postgresql/query-planner/&t=Interactive%20PostgreSQL%20Query%20Planner%20Visualizer" target="_blank" class="share-btn">🟧 Hacker News</a>
  </div>
</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .viz-container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .viz-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .viz-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, #60a5fa, #a78bfa, #34d399);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .section-desc {
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* Overview */
  .overview-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .overview-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.1), rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.05));
    border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #ccc;
  }

  .overview-card strong { color: #fff; }
  .overview-card em { color: #60a5fa; font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }
  .overview-card a { color: #60a5fa; }

  /* Action Buttons */
  .action-btn {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .action-btn:disabled {
    opacity: 0.4;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  .primary-btn {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a78bfa, #7c3aed);
    color: white;
  }

  .primary-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.4);
  }

  .step-btn {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #60a5fa, #3b82f6);
    color: white;
  }

  .reset-btn {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    color: #aaa;
  }

  .reset-btn:hover { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2); color: #fff; }

  /* Flow Section */
  .flow-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  /* Explanation Cards */
  .explain-section {
    margin-bottom: 50px;
  }

  .explain-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 24px;
  }

  .explain-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .explain-card p {
    color: #aaa;
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .explain-card strong { color: #00d4ff; }
  .explain-card em { color: #a78bfa; }
  .explain-card code {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #22c55e;
  }

  .highlight-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08), rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.08));
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
  }

  /* Sliders shared */
  input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%;
    height: 8px;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #a78bfa;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  /* Checkboxes */
  .scan-check, .join-check, .strategy-check {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .scan-check label, .join-check label, .strategy-check label {
    color: #ccc;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  input[type="checkbox"] {
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    accent-color: #a78bfa;
  }

  /* ===== Section 1: Scan Types ===== */
  .scan-controls {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .scan-slider {
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .scan-slider label {
    display: block;
    color: #ccc;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .scan-slider strong { color: #a78bfa; }

  .scan-result {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .scan-chosen {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .scan-chosen-label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #888;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .scan-chosen-name {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #60a5fa;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .scan-chosen-reason {
    color: #aaa;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .scan-comparison {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 12px;
  }

  :global(.scan-cost-bar) {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 12px 8px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  :global(.scan-cost-bar.chosen) {
    background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.4);
    box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.15);
  }

  :global(.scan-cost-bar.disabled) {
    opacity: 0.3;
  }

  :global(.scan-cost-name) {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #888;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  :global(.scan-cost-value) {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Menlo', monospace;
  }

  .scan-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .scan-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }

  :global(.scan-card.active) {
    border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.5);
    background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08);
  }

  .scan-card-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .scan-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .scan-card p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #888;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .scan-card code {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 1px 4px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #22c55e;
  }

  /* ===== Section 2: Join Strategies ===== */
  .join-controls {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .join-slider {
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .join-slider label {
    display: block;
    color: #ccc;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .join-slider strong { color: #a78bfa; }

  .join-result {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 24px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .join-chosen {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .join-chosen-label {
